{
  "text": "In addition to the Sst I, other variations are noted in the promoter region of the apoC-III gene ( Fig. 1 ). More specifically, the C-482T and T-455C variants are located within an insulin response element (IRE) of the apoC-III gene [CITATION_1] . These two apoC-III promoter polymorphisms have been shown to inactivate a negative IRE located between nucleotides Ϫ 449 and Ϫ 490 [CITATION_2] , and are in linkage disequilibrium with the apoC-III Sst I polymorphism [CITATION_3] . In addition, variation at the C-482T position has been shown to influence the glucose and insulin response to an oral glucose tolerance test (OGTT), carriers of the C-482T rare allele having significantly elevated glucose and insulin concentrations following the glucose challenge [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "39650314",
